# Week 8 — Final Integration & System Demonstration

## Overview

Week 8 represents the **final phase of the ICS-RedSim project**, where all components of the virtual ICS security lab are integrated and validated.
The objective of this phase is to demonstrate the complete workflow of the system, including **industrial process operation, security incident simulation, and detection using monitoring tools**.

This stage verifies that the ICS environment can successfully simulate industrial security incidents while allowing monitoring tools to detect abnormal activity.

---

# Objectives

The key objectives of Week 8 include:

* Integrate all lab components
* Perform end-to-end system validation
* Demonstrate attack detection capability
* Collect and organize project evidence
* Prepare final project documentation and demo

---

# Integrated System Architecture

The complete ICS-RedSim environment includes multiple layers that work together to simulate and monitor industrial operations.

### System Components

| Component  | Role                                    |
| ---------- | --------------------------------------- |
| OpenPLC    | Simulated programmable logic controller |
| FUXA       | SCADA/HMI monitoring interface          |
| Suricata   | Network intrusion detection system      |
| Wazuh      | Security monitoring and log analysis    |
| Wireshark  | Network traffic analysis                |
| Kali Linux | Controlled attack simulation            |

These components together form a **virtual ICS cybersecurity testbed**.

---

# End-to-End System Workflow

The final system workflow demonstrates how industrial monitoring and security detection operate together.

```
Normal Process Operation
        ↓
SCADA Monitoring
        ↓
Security Incident Simulation
        ↓
Network Traffic Analysis
        ↓
IDS Alert Generation
        ↓
Security Monitoring Dashboard
```

This workflow illustrates how abnormal activity can be detected within industrial networks.

---

# System Demonstration

The final demonstration includes the following steps:

### Step 1 — Normal Operation

* SCADA dashboard displays tank level
* Pump control operates normally
* PLC executes process logic
* No IDS alerts generated

### Step 2 — Incident Simulation

Controlled security scenarios are executed from the testing machine.

Examples include:

* Network scanning
* Abnormal Modbus traffic
* Traffic bursts

### Step 3 — Detection

Monitoring tools detect abnormal behavior.

* Suricata generates network alerts
* Wazuh displays security events
* Wireshark captures abnormal packets

### Step 4 — Evidence Collection

Evidence is collected to document the system response.

